tervention, metrics, and diagnostics context produced by\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:33:tests, metadata directories, metadata index entries, stats, execution metrics,\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:51:parameters its workflow's metrics actually produce. The subsections below state\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:59:generation metrics — strategy, agent, and model; input, cached-input, and output\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:61:metrics; metadata-entry counts; and dynamic-access coverage with its supporting\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:75:the agent generation metrics above, a stats comparison for the bumped version,\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:78:in workflow identity (compilation vs. runtime wording), the metrics file, and\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:84:workflow is metadata-first and does not produce agent token metrics, so its body\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:93:No generation happened, so the body has no generation metrics. It states why the\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:100:title and body that reads the same metrics and repository evidence used by live\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:112:references, review text, metrics summaries, and human-intervention visibility.\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:122:across chunks and preserves it until the final PR closes it. The exhaust report\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:20:produces a locally verified pull request with metrics and enough context for\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:91:must keep separate metrics and review evidence so maintainers can distinguish\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:100:| **Forge metrics directory** | The `forge/` subdirectory of the reachability checkout, used as the transient staging area for a run's in-flight metrics (`.pending_metrics.json`) until the PR step reads them. Durable per-library run metrics persist to `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json` (§FS-forge-run-metrics). |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:103:| **Workflow driver** | Deterministic script in the `drivers/` subdirectory of [ai_workflows/](../ai_workflows/) that prepares the working environment, directories, branch/context, strategy bundle, workflow engine, agent, and metrics for one claimed unit of work. The driver runs Forge plumbing; Codex or another LLM agent should not decide that setup during a generated run. Specified by §WF-forge-workflow-drivers. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:106:| **Post-generation intervention** | The built-in recovery sequence the workflow base class runs when the post-iteration `./gradlew test` still fails during finalization. It is a fixed Codex-then-Pi lane, not a pluggable registry and not selected per strategy: a Codex metadata fix runs first (using the `fix-missing-reachability-metadata` skill, pinned to the run's GraalVM); only if that does not recover does Pi remove the offending failing tests as a last resort. When recovery makes the post-generation test pass, the run reports `SUCCESS_WITH_INTERVENTION_STATUS` and the intervention record (stage, intervention file, analysis) is saved for the run metrics and PR body. The base class runs this lane once per GraalVM test lane (current defaults and `future-defaults-all` on the latest GraalVM, plus current defaults on the GraalVM 25 toolchain). |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:138:  The Forge metrics directory is derived from it as the `forge/` subdirectory.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:186:  `forge/` when the workflow records metrics, logs, or resumable state.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:189:  context must preserve the complete reachability repo before running any\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:195:- **Per-run metrics record** persisted to\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:196:  `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json`, as required by\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:197:  §FS-forge-run-metrics.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:210:### FS-forge-run-metrics: Per-run metrics record\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:213:Every run must persist a per-library metrics record to\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:214:`stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json` so cost, token,\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:216:(§GOAL-maximize-library-coverage). During a run, in-flight metrics are staged\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:217:transiently in the Forge metrics directory as `.pending_metrics.json` and\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:219:instead record durable, schema-validated metrics under\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:259:metrics and PR description. A task must not open a PR, mark a project item\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:262:complete either tier, the workflow must return `RUN_STATUS_FAILURE` and preserve\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:288:reasons no single-library generation could have settled: they depend on\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:315:`human-intervention` and the verification metrics and PR description must list\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:347:reported as infrastructure failures, retried or preserved with diagnostics as\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:440:| `SUCCESS_WITH_INTERVENTION_STATUS` | Tests succeeded after the built-in post-generation recovery modified the working tree (a Codex metadata fix, then Pi removing failing tests as a last resort), and the local CI-equivalent verification (§FS-local-ci-equivalent-verification) passed. The intervention's record is included in the run-metrics and PR description. PR-eligible; distinct from the `human-intervention` label unless §FS-human-intervention-policy separately requires that label. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:504:of §GOAL-maximize-library-coverage), dynamic-access, and metadata metrics.\nforge/docs/grund.md:10:queues into locally verified pull requests with tests, metadata, metrics, and\nforge/docs/grund.md:11:human-readable context, while preserving review and repository CI as the final\nforge/docs/benchmarking.md:10:`benchmark_run_metrics/`\nforge/docs/benchmarking.md:18:verification, and benchmark metrics in one comparable process\nforge/docs/benchmarking.md:39:Benchmarking must preserve every